						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in front of the temple of Vīrabhadra.</hi></p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra—A.D. 1289.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record belonging to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandradēva</hi> is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1211, Virōdhi, Āsvija ba. 6, Thursday,</hi> corresponding regularly to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1289, October 6, Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the death of a hero (name lost) in a fight. He is stated to be the son of <hi rend="bold">Vasuva-Nāyaka.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
